x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/freedom-day-nightclubs-getty-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/freedom-day-nightclubs-getty-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>金斯顿 Pryzm 的老板表示，英国夜总会普遍关闭的原因之一是“年轻人喝酒少了”。 </p><ul><li data-leveltext="" data-font="Symbol" data-listid="281" data-list-defn-props="{&quot;335552541&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335559684&quot;:-2,&quot;335559685&quot;:720,&quot;335559991&quot;:360,&quot;469769226&quot;:&quot;Symbol&quot;,&quot;469769242&quot;:[8226],&quot;469777803&quot;:&quot;left&quot;,&quot;469777804&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;469777815&quot;:&quot;hybridMultilevel&quot;}" aria-setsize="-1" data-aria-posinset="1" data-aria-level="1"><b>阅读更多：</b><b> </b><a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/2023-was-worst-year-for-venue-closures-while-no-one-in-music-industry-seems-to-care-say-mvt-3562266"><b>MVT 表示，2023 年是“场馆关闭最糟糕的一年”，而“音乐行业似乎没有人关心”</b></a></li></ul><p>上个月，在拥有<a href="https://www.pryzm.co.uk/">Pryzm</a>和<a href="https://www.atikclub.co.uk/">Atik</a>品牌的所有者<a href="https://rekomgroup.com/brands">Rekom UK</a>进入破产管理程序后<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/owners-of-uks-pryzm-and-atik-nightclubs-call-in-administrators-3571633">，金士顿 Pryzm 的未来受到质疑</a>。该公司列举了过去一年夜间行业面临的挑战，将其问题归咎于能源价格上涨和学生因当前生活成本而削减开支。</p><p>然而，上周， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/banquet-records-announces-that-kingston-pryzm-is-saved-3581452">Banquet Records 证实，经常举办“户外”演出的 Kingston Pryzm</a>场地<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/banquet-records-announces-that-kingston-pryzm-is-saved-3581452">将继续开放</a>，尽管其业主已致电管理员。 </p><figure id="attachment_3571673" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3571673" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3571673" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/RekomPryzm-Atik-administration-.jpg" alt="Pryzm 夜总会的外观" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/RekomPryzm-Atik-administration-.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/RekomPryzm-Atik-administration--400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/RekomPryzm-Atik-administration--800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/RekomPryzm-Atik-administration--696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/RekomPryzm-Atik-administration--1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/RekomPryzm-Atik-administration--1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3571673" class="wp-caption-text">普里兹姆夜总会。图片来源：Chris Eades/Getty</figcaption></figure><p>现在，Rekon 英国首席执行官彼得·马克斯 (Peter Marks) 告诉<a href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-68295306" target="_blank" rel="noopener">BBC</a> ，由于饮酒习惯的改变、生活成本危机和房租价格飙升，年轻人和学生的外出次数比以往任何时候都少。</p><p>他说：“许多过去每月支付 800 英镑住宿费的学生现在面临着每月 1,200 英镑的[更高租金]。” “显然，人们仍然喜欢外出，[但是]如果资金紧张，[他们]会晚点来，所以他们会晚点到达我们家门口，而且花的钱也会更少。”</p><p> “我晚上7点到11点之间走了一圈，城里的人不超过200人。两年前，这里真的非常繁忙和热闹。”</p><p> Banquet Records 定期在该场地举办亲密的专辑发行演出，并举办过<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/billie-eilish">Billie Eilish</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-1975">The 1975</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/boygenius">Boygenius 等乐队的演出，</a>而<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/future-islands">Future Island</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/yard-act">Yard Act</a>等乐队也计划在未来在这里演出。</p><p>本周<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/31-per-cent-of-uk-nightclubs-closed-last-year-as-industry-demands-government-action-3587334">公布的统计数据显示，过去三年英国约 31% 的夜总会被迫关闭</a>。夜间产业协会呼吁政府立即采取行动应对危机，指出“夜总会行业深刻且系统性的边缘化”，这对“我们文化景观的活力”构成了威胁。</p><p> 1月份发布的另一份报告显示<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/report-shows-disaster-facing-grassroots-music-venues-the-big-companies-and-arenas-are-now-going-to-have-to-answer-for-this-3576307">，2023年英国草根音乐场馆将遭遇“灾难”</a> ，要求对更大的场馆征收门票税以及更广泛的行业进行投资的呼声越来越高。报告指出，核心问题是能源价格飙升、房东提高地税金额、供应成本、营业费率、许可问题、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/manchester-night-day-cardiff-fuel-post-lockdown-noise-complaints-venues-3103934">噪音投诉</a>以及<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-venue-trust-thank-help-gigs-return-2021-2842425">COVID-19 的持续冲击波</a>。</p><p>去年，音乐场馆信托基金<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-venue-trust-annual-report-government-action-arena-investment-frank-turner-talent-pipeline-3389434">在议会大厦提交了第一份年度报告，警告英国的草根演出空间正在“走向悬崖”，</a>除非政府采取紧急行动和新的大型场馆的投资。在发出严厉警告称<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/uk-to-lose-10-per-cent-of-grassroots-venues-in-2023-as-calls-grow-for-rest-of-industry-to-invest-3499727">英国将在 2023 年失去 10% 的草根音乐场馆后，</a> MVT 和该行业的其他人士在年底<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/2023-was-worst-year-for-venue-closures-while-no-one-in-music-industry-seems-to-care-say-mvt-3562266">告诉<i>NME</i> 2023 年是“场馆关闭最糟糕的一年</a>”，而“没有人音乐界似乎很关心”。</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/pryzm-boss-blames-young-people-drinking-less-for-nightclub-closures-3588126">Pryzm 老板将夜店关闭归咎于“年轻人少喝酒”，该消息</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
